.TH "libnvme_generate_tls_key_identity" 9 "libnvme_generate_tls_key_identity" "April 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvme_generate_tls_key_identity \- Generate the TLS key identity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" libnvme_generate_tls_key_identity
.BI "(struct libnvme_global_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "const char *hostnqn "  ","
.BI "const char *subsysnqn "  ","
.BI "int version "  ","
.BI "int hmac "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *configured_key "  ","
.BI "int key_len "  ","
.BI "char **identity "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
struct libnvme_global_ctx object
.IP "hostnqn" 12
Host NVMe Qualified Name
.IP "subsysnqn" 12
Subsystem NVMe Qualified Name
.IP "version" 12
Key version to use
.IP "hmac" 12
HMAC algorithm
.IP "configured_key" 12
Configured key data to derive the key from
.IP "key_len" 12
Length of \fIconfigured_key\fP
.IP "identity" 12
TLS identity to return
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Derives a 'retained' TLS key as specified in NVMe TCP and
generate the corresponding TLs identity.

It is the responsibility of the caller to free the returned string.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or negative error code otherwise
